n conceptual and social aspects of pluricentric variation and other forms of language-internal variation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLanguage and languagesxVariation. 0aSociolinguistics. 0aStandard language. 4aKognitive Linguistik. 4aPlurizentrische Sprachen. 4aSoziolinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCognitive Linguistics.  aCorpus-based Methods.  aLanguage Variation.  aPluricentric Languages.  aSociolinguistics.1 aAuer, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Hertog, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeeraerts, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeylen, Kris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aImpe, Leen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKretzenbacher, Heinz L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKristiansen, Gitte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLópez-García, Ángel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLüdi, Georges, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorrby, Catrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuette, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider, Edgar W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilva, Augusto Soares da, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoares da Silva, Augusto, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSpeelman, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete Engli